-- Indian shares fall to near 2-month closing low; cyclical stocks drag
-- By Indulal PM
-- Tue Oct 07, 2014 06:10AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Oct 7 (Reuters) - Indian shares fell for a second straight session on Tuesday, marking their lowest closing level in nearly two months, as cyclical stocks such as Hindalco Industries <HALC.NS> declined ahead of the earnings season.

The benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> provisionally fell 1.08 percent to 26,280.63, while the broader NSE index <.NSEI> ended down 1.17 percent at 7,852.40.